## Next.js patterns
- Default to **Server Components**; use `'use client'` only when needed (state, effects, events).
- Data loading: server-side fetch in page/layout when possible; client fetch only for live interactions.
- Keep pages thin: move UI into `components/` and logic into hooks/utilities.

## Tailwind patterns
- Prefer composition: `clsx`/`cn` helper (if exists) over long ternaries.
- Use semantic class groupings: layout → spacing → typography → color → effects.
- Avoid inline arbitrary values unless there is a clear reason.

## Component structure
- One component = one responsibility; extract subcomponents when JSX > ~120 lines.
- Props: prefer explicit props over passing large objects; type props строго.
- Accessibility: interactive elements must be `button/a/input` (not `div` with onClick).
